Example is bucket list/countries.


1. Create structure;
top_level/client/build
in client/build/ create:
bundle.js (empty file)
style.css (can be empty or populated)
index.html (Basic page set up, headers, drop downs script src='bundle.js')


top_level/src/package.json
              webpack.config.js*
top_level/src/countries/(or accounts, or banks etc)
              app.js (onload, handle countries, display)
              country_view.js



Installs
========
toplevel:
npm init (creates package.json)
toplevel/client/
npm init (creates package.json)
npm install --save -dev webpack
npm install --save mongo
npm install --save mongodb
mongod (run mongo)
npm install --save -dev express
nom install --save -dev body-parser

toplevel/client/
webpack -w (run webpack)

bucket_list/client/ webpack -w

toplevel type mongo
starts database.


==================================
==================================


use app.js t console log out some stuff and ensure pafe loads etc.





*webpack.config.js
config = {
  entry: "./src/app.js",
  output: {
    filename: "bundle.js",
    path:"./build"
},
devtool: 'source-map'
}

module.exports = config;